The paper deals with a preference relation over admissible solutions, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses propositional theories and minimal models, which are topics in logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The algorithm proposed in the paper is based on unsatisfiable core analysis, which is a technique used in constraint satisfaction and optimization (cs.DS). Finally, the paper compares the performance of the proposed algorithm with other solvers, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE).
